           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-11">Sruk Kandaṅ: Si Paṁnaṅ, Gho Kañcin, Gho Prāṇa, Gho Śvatī, Gho Ditātsava, Gho Kaṁpañ, Gho Drānandana, Gho Prajñadhirāja, Gho Kañjes, Gho Kansip, Gho Kaṁbhū, Gho Bhāva, Gho Vara, Gho Panlas, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Pandan, Gho Kaṁpit, Gho Kanlah, Gho Kanso, Gho Kañcū, Gho Gandha, Gho Kanleṅ, another Gho Kaṁbhū, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Taṅkū, Gho Tīrtha, <gap reason="lost"/> nandana, Gvāl Kandeṅ, Gvāl Kañcaṅ paṅ, Gvāl Kaṁvai, Tai khmau, Tai Agat, Tai Kan-ak, <foreign>tai a</foreign> 1, Tai Kaṁvai, Tai Hyaṅ Candana, Tai Kañcū accompanied by two children <supplied reason="explanation">Lap Dīrgha and a <foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>. Total: 28 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 3 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 6 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a female slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai a</foreign></supplied>, a slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, a boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>; grand total 40.</p>
              <p n="12-18"><gap reason="lost"/>, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kaṁvaḥ, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kaṁsip Khñuṁ accompanied by two baby-girls <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied> and a son <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied> called Paṁnaṅ. Total: 9 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, an animal keeper <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 6 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a slave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, a boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, 3 baby-girls <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied> and 3 girls <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai a</foreign></supplied>; grand total 24.</p>
              <p n="18-30">Ruined. <supplied reason="subaudible">Gvāl</supplied> Kandeṅ, another <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl Chke, Gvāl Kañjan, Tai Thgan, Tai Kaṁpit, Tai Kanteṅ, Tai Agat, Tai Saṁ-ap, Tai Dharmma, Tai Panlas, Tai Kanhyaṅ, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Ruined.</p>
